overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing detailed specifications and a Statement of Work. The
  agent first conducted a thorough analysis of the existing codebase against
  these requirements, identifying key missing features such as a tiredness
  severity scale, COMISA detection, and insufficient sleep syndrome detection.
  Following this review, the agent developed and executed a plan to implement
  these missing functionalities. This involved updating data types, validation
  schemas, UI components for input, and the logic for generating both the
  on-screen and PDF reports, ensuring that appropriate messaging and
  recommendations were included for each new detection. The implementation
  focused on integrating these features seamlessly into the existing application
  structure.
